msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:1118
msgid "The thumbwheels in the upper rightmost part of the DDD panel are used to control the AN/AWG-9 radar emitter's frequency (**13**) and the missile control channel used with the AIM-7 and AIM-54 (**14**). Adjustment of these might be needed to avoid interference from other AN/AWG-9 equipped aircraft or other external sources. The WCS reads the missile channel for the AIM-7 as the missiles are prepared as they need to be tuned and changing the channel after this will not affect a change unless the preparation sequence is restarted."
