#: ../../source/general.rst:1239
msgid "Tactical Information Display (TID) and Associated Controls"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:1242
msgid "The TID is the main data display for the WCS. It displays a tactical picture to the RIO which is used to identify and select targets for the long range weapons on the F-14 Tomcat. Think of it as a top down map showing the relative coordinates of all presented tracks and symbols, but without a representation of the ground/surface features (map). It is also used in secondary roles as a display for entering data into the WCS, for navigation, for INS alignment and for the on board checkout, OBC."
