msgid "Select CAP category TAC DATA."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:3618
msgid "Depress HOME BASE and enter aircraft longitude and latitude via the CAP data entry buttons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:3620
msgid "Aircraft latitude and longitude can be entered directly through the following steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:3622
msgid "Set the NAV MODE switch to either OFF or GND ALIGN."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:3623
msgid "Select CAP category NAV."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:3625
msgid "Depress OWN A/C and enter aircraft longitude and latitude via the CAP data entry buttons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:3627
msgid "Depressing OWN A/C hooks own aircraft. If longitude and latitude is entered with the NAV MODE switch set to OFF, own aircraft must be hooked when the NAV MODE switch is set from OFF to GND ALIGN again. Be aware that whatever has been hooked (OWN AC or HB) will provide the data that is entered when NAV MODE is set from OFF to GND ALIGN."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:3629
msgid "For a reference alignment, alignment has to reach fine align complete. Both CVA ALIGN and GND ALIGN can be used to establish a reference alignment. The reference alignment is complete when a dot appears in the diamond."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:3632
msgid "To establish a reference alignment follow these steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:3634
msgid "WCS switch - STBY."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:3635
msgid "NAV MODE - CVA or GND."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:3636
msgid "DATA LINK - ON (CV ops only)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:3637
msgid "D/L MODE - CAINS/WAYPT (CV ops only)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:3638
msgid "Reference alignment continues to fine align complete."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:3640
msgid "To store the reference alignment: 6.      NAV MODE switch to INS. 7.      WCS - OFF. NAV MODE - OFF."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:3645
msgid "Unstable current or temporary loss of power will cause the CAINS to be deselected and will be indicated by a flashing HS acronym. A reference alignment cannot be done through a handset alignment, even if continued to fine align complete. For a successful reference alignment the aircraft must not move and the parking brake must not be cycled after the reference heading has been stored. For a valid reference alignment, it isn’t necessary to switch NAV MODE to INS, instead it can be switched directly to OFF from either CVA or GND ALIGN."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:3649
msgid "Catapult Alignment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/general.rst:3651
msgid "The CAT ALIGN mode is used to prevent suspend align when positioned on the catapult and the parking brake bas been released. The purpose of the catapult align mode is to provide normal CVA ALIGN as long as possible. When CAT ALIGN is selected, large roll, pitch, speed and heading changes of the ship can cause the program to automatically switch to INS."
