#: ../../source/general.rst:4456
msgid "The HUD and VDIG will then provide vertical and lateral precision course vector symbols, forming crossed pointers that are driven by the ICLS. On the HUD, full-scale vector deflection is limited to 2°. Full-scale vector deflection on the VDI is 1.5°. In the AWL/PCD submode of LDG, the HSD will additionally display TACAN information if the HSD is set to NAV mode on the PDCP."
